  "sourceVersion": "Regio Midi application v1.7",
  "notes": "3-pipe / change-over zone (FCU) controller with built-in CO2 sensor, room temperature sensor, occupancy button and 3 universal outputs (analogue heating/cooling/VAV or thermal actuators, plus EC-fan or forced ventilation). Designed for multi-slave deployment under a Moxa Modbus master (RC1, RC2, ...). Naming is intentionally flattened to TWO STEMS per RC so the WebPort diagram view shows one main symbol per controller plus one VAV/airflow symbol — all controller-level tags share the form `{prefix}_<TOKEN>` (stem `{prefix}`) and all airflow tags share `{prefix}_VAV_<TOKEN>` (stem `{prefix}_VAV`). Standard suffix separators (_PV, _HAL, _HSP) are baked into the token (e.g. HEATOP, CO2HSP, SUPPLYMAXH) to keep stems flat. Modbus register addressing follows WebPort convention: Discrete inputs = 10000+offset, Coils = 0+offset, Input registers = 30000+offset, Holding registers = 40000+offset (PDF lists 1-based offsets). Models in the Regio Midi family (per PDF Appendix): COVERED here as register-compatible siblings sharing the same Modbus map: RCC-C3DOCS / RCC-C3DOCS-BLACK (built-in CO2, primary target), RCC-C3HCS (built-in CO2 + hidden setpoint, no occupancy button), RC-C3DOC / RC-C3DOC-BLACK (external CO2 input on AI2), RC-C3DFOC (CO2 + EC fan), RC-C3 / RC-C3O / RC-C3H (basic 3-output, no CO2 — set CO2 sensor option to off). NOT COVERED — separate templates needed: RC-CF / RC-CFO / RC-CDFO (3-step fan-coil with DO1-DO3 fan relays — different output map), RC-CT / RC-CTH / RC-CTO / RC-CDTO (3-point increase/decrease valve control on DO1-DO5 — different output topology). multiSlave flag set so the userscript prepends slave id to each address.",
  "defaultDevicePrefix": "RC",
  "multiSlave": true,

